# Verification

> How we prove the project works. `<%= it.verifyCmd %>` runs these as one cross-platform gate (non-zero exit on failure) and is wired into <% if (it.runtime === "opencode") { %>the `.opencode/plugins/reins-verify.ts` plugin<% } else { %>Claude Code hooks<% } %>.

## Levels

1. **Lint** — `<%= it.commands.lint || "(configure in reins.config.json)" %>`
2. **Unit tests** — `<%= it.commands.test || "(configure in reins.config.json)" %>`
<% if (it.commands.typecheck) { %>3. **Type check** — `<%= it.commands.typecheck %>`
<% } %><% if (it.commands.e2e) { %>4. **End-to-end** — `<%= it.commands.e2e %>`
<% } %>5. **Security** — dependency audit + secret scan (`<%= it.verifyCmd %> --only security`).
6. **Design** — a deterministic "AI slop" scan of UI files (`<%= it.verifyCmd %> --only design`); skips when there are no UI files. Pairs with the `design-reviewer`'s judgment (`docs/design.md`).
7. **Feature list** — the state machine is coherent (at most one `in_progress`).
<% if (it.isSdd) { %>8. **Traceability** — every requirement maps to at least one test.
<% } %>

## Rules

- The required checks (see `reins.config.json` → `verify.required`) must pass before a feature is `done`.
<% if (it.runtime === "opencode") { %>- The `reins-verify` plugin runs `<%= it.verifyCmd %>` on `file.edited` and `session.idle` and reports a red tree. (opencode cannot hard-block a finished session — treat a failing gate as "not done".)
<% } else { %>- The `Stop` hook runs `<%= it.verifyCmd %>` and blocks the session from ending on a red tree.
<% } %>- Never mark a feature `done` with a failing required check.
- CI runs the same gate (`.github/workflows/reins-verify.yml`). A ghost install (`reins init --ghost`) keeps nothing in git, so there is no committed workflow — the local hooks remain the enforcement.
